never meet again,

00:13:27.515 --> 00:13:30.453
let me leave you with
some words of wisdom.

00:13:30.487 --> 00:13:34.996
That man who is doing everything
in his power to manipulate you,

00:13:35.030 --> 00:13:37.334
do you have any idea what
he's really after?

00:13:37.367 --> 00:13:38.403
- Huh?

00:13:38.436 --> 00:13:42.276
- It's obvious he wants
to dominate you--

00:13:42.310 --> 00:13:45.951
control every aspect
of your life.

00:13:45.984 --> 00:13:49.224
SHIZUKA: Your free will is yours
and yours alone, Akira.

00:13:49.258 --> 00:13:52.430
Your freedom to choose
your own path in life,

00:13:52.464 --> 00:13:55.538
the self respect you need
to live your life,

00:13:55.571 --> 00:13:58.108
your soul,
your pride...

00:13:59.345 --> 00:14:01.983
He wants you to abandon all
of those.

00:14:02.016 --> 00:14:06.125
That man has no self esteem
and he'll never be satisfied.

00:14:06.158 --> 00:14:08.597
He'll keep putting others down
in order

00:14:08.630 --> 00:14:11.201
to make himself seem bigger
to the people he controls

00:14:11.234 --> 00:14:13.807
around him.
Can't you see?

00:14:13.840 --> 00:14:15.745
That pathetic man
will do anything

00:14:15.778 --> 00:14:17.982
to assert himself
and get a brief sense

00:14:18.015 --> 00:14:20.052
of fulfillment by demeaning you.

00:14:20.721 --> 00:14:22.057
Until today,

00:14:22.090 --> 00:14:25.029
I was no different from you.

00:14:25.062 --> 00:14:28.536
But you were the one
who finally opened my eyes!

00:14:29.572 --> 00:14:31.642
I'm done taking orders.

00:14:32.879 --> 00:14:34.648
I'm making my own choices!

00:14:35.751 --> 00:14:37.655
Do you need to leave?

00:14:37.689 --> 00:14:39.659
Do you need to stay?

00:14:39.692 --> 00:14:41.562
With the way the world
is right now,

00:14:41.596 --> 00:14:45.804
no one can be certain of what
the right decision to make is.

00:14:45.837 --> 00:14:49.779
Even so,
I know what decision I'm making!

00:14:49.812 --> 00:14:51.716
There's no doubt in my mind.

00:14:51.749 --> 00:14:54.254
I'm leaving this place
and getting away

00:14:54.287 --> 00:14:58.095
from this disgusting
jackass as soon as possible!

00:14:59.766 --> 00:15:01.201
- [grunts]

00:15:01.970 --> 00:15:03.306
- [exhales]

00:15:03.339 --> 00:15:04.642
- I tell ya,

00:15:04.675 --> 00:15:06.613
this is why women
are troublesome.

00:15:06.646 --> 00:15:10.420
Once they go into hysterics,
there's no use talkin' to 'em.

00:15:10.453 --> 00:15:13.059
KOSUGI: Right, everyone?
[all grunting]

00:15:13.092 --> 00:15:14.695
- What's it gonna be, Akira?

00:15:14.729 --> 00:15:16.933
It's your choice to make.

00:15:16.966 --> 00:15:19.037
You're not a machine
or a zombie.

00:15:19.070 --> 00:15:20.941
You're still human,
aren't you?

00:15:23.613 --> 00:15:25.618
Tell me what you want.

00:15:25.651 --> 00:15:26.753
Well, Akira?

00:15:26.786 --> 00:15:28.623
- [gasping]

00:15:38.309 --> 00:15:40.113
[gasps]

00:15:40.146 --> 00:15:42.785
KOSUGI: How long are you gonna
keep spoutin' nonsense?

00:15:42.818 --> 00:15:44.221
Give me that!
- [gasps]

00:15:44.254 --> 00:15:46.526
KOSUGI: Who cares about what
you want to do?

00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:47.862
You don't need this!

00:15:47.895 --> 00:15:49.532
- [gasping]

00:15:52.805 --> 00:15:55.811
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

00:15:55.844 --> 00:15:57.815
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:15:57.848 --> 00:15:59.250
[gasps]

00:16:04.762 --> 00:16:06.264
[gasping]

00:16:13.980 --> 00:16:15.182
[gasps]

00:16:16.017 --> 00:16:17.988
[both grunting]

00:16:18.021 --> 00:16:19.859
[AKIRA gasping]

00:16:19.893 --> 00:16:22.263
- [gasps]

00:16:22.297 --> 00:16:24.434
KOSUGI: Wh--What do you think
you're doing?

00:16:24.467 --> 00:16:27.373
Who--who gave you permission
to retaliate?

00:16:27.406 --> 00:16:28.944
AKIRA: Chief...

00:16:28.977 --> 00:16:30.480
I'm thankful.

00:16:30.514 --> 00:16:34.054
You have taken care
of me in my time of need.

00:16:34.087 --> 00:16:37.093
But this is where
we part ways.

00:16:37.127 --> 00:16:39.565
I want nothing
to do with you.

00:16:41.301 --> 00:16:44.341
.And I hope to never see
your face again!

00:16:44.374 --> 00:16:46.847
- [groaning]

00:16:46.880 --> 00:16:48.482
- [chuckles]

00:16:48.516 --> 00:16:52.023
- You still owe me,
and you owe me a lot!

00:16:52.056 --> 00:16:53.861
- I won't make it up to you!

00:16:53.894 --> 00:16:55.797
Sorry about that, chief!

00:16:55.831 --> 00:16:58.202
KOSUGI: That's irresponsible
of you!

00:16:58.236 --> 00:16:59.539
AKIRA: My apologies!

00:16:59.572 --> 00:17:01.676
KOSUGI: I helped you
in your time of need!

00:17:01.710 --> 00:17:02.912
AKIRA: My apologies!

00:17:02.945 --> 00:17:04.782
- You'll come to regret this.

00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:07.555
The moment you set foot outside
the safety of this camp,

00:17:07.588 --> 00:17:09.224
you'll be nothin'
but zombie fodder!

00:17:09.257 --> 00:17:11.696
KOSUGI: Mark my words!

00:17:11.729 --> 00:17:14.735
AKIRA: Hey, it's fine by me.

00:17:14.769 --> 00:17:17.173
It's better than being worked
like a zombie

00:17:17.207 --> 00:17:19.745
and not do the things
I wanna do!

00:17:21.583 --> 00:17:23.285
MAN: Hey, check it out!

00:17:23.318 --> 00:17:26.392
The supply
gathering team's back!

00:17:26.425 --> 00:17:28.796
We pulled in a large haul today,
boss!

00:17:28.830 --> 00:17:29.966
[snickers]

00:17:29.999 --> 00:17:32.069
Come on over and check this out.

00:17:32.103 --> 00:17:34.440
You're not gonna believe
how much stuff we go--

00:17:34.474 --> 00:17:35.811
[screams]

00:17:35.844 --> 00:17:37.013
[all gasping]

00:17:37.046 --> 00:17:40.085
[all yelling]

00:17:40.119 --> 00:17:43.091
- Calm down!
It's just one zombie!

00:17:43.125 --> 00:17:45.564
Just stay cool and and grab--
- It's now or never!

00:17:45.597 --> 00:17:46.431
- Wait!

00:17:46.464 --> 00:17:48.570
- I don't wanna be eaten alive!

00:17:48.604 --> 00:17:50.507
[shouting]

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:51.576
[metal crashing]

00:17:51.609 --> 00:17:53.914
[zombies roaring]

00:17:53.947 --> 00:17:55.951
- [shouting]

00:17:55.984 --> 00:17:57.922
- [panicked screaming]

00:17:57.955 --> 00:18:00.292
- [shouting]

00:18:02.965 --> 00:18:05.870
MAN: Thank you,
thank you!

00:18:05.904 --> 00:18:06.873
AKIRA: Kencho!
[both gasping]

00:18:06.906 --> 00:18:08.142
AKIRA: Shizuka!

00:18:08.175 --> 00:18:09.946
- We're fine over here!

00:18:09.979 --> 00:18:12.083
- Grab my hand!
Hurry!

00:18:12.116 --> 00:18:13.620
- [screaming]
- [zombie grunts]

00:18:13.653 --> 00:18:15.624
KENCHO: Dammit!
Dammit!

00:18:15.657 --> 00:18:18.028
I'm not gonna be able
to save them all!

00:18:18.062 --> 00:18:19.699
[KOSUGI screaming]
- [gasps]

00:18:19.732 --> 00:18:21.401
- [gasps]
Stay back!

00:18:21.435 --> 00:18:23.238
Turn back!

00:18:23.271 --> 00:18:27.046
Keep away from me,
you hideous freaks of nature!

00:18:27.080 --> 00:18:29.618
- [breathing heavily]
Chief!

00:18:29.652 --> 00:18:31.756
[gasping]

00:18:34.996 --> 00:18:37.166
[gasping]

00:18:38.937 --> 00:18:41.041
AKIRA: The food truck.

00:18:41.075 --> 00:18:42.210
[exhales]

00:18:42.243 --> 00:18:43.680
[inhales deeply]

00:18:44.849 --> 00:18:46.385
[grunts]

00:18:46.418 --> 00:18:48.790
[grunts]
Hey, delivery team!

00:18:48.823 --> 00:18:50.460
I have an idea!

00:18:50.493 --> 00:18:52.831
Can I count on you to help?

00:18:52.864 --> 00:18:54.467
[KOSUGI panting]

00:18:54.502 --> 00:18:58.643
I'm not built for running!

00:18:58.676 --> 00:19:00.412
[KOSUGI grunts]

00:19:00.446 --> 00:19:03.052
[groaning]

00:19:03.085 --> 00:19:05.790
[screaming]

00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:10.634
[gasping]

00:19:10.667 --> 00:19:12.203
KOSUGI: Tendo?

00:19:12.838 --> 00:19:14.107
- Chief Kosugi!

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:15.276
Now's our chance!

00:19:15.309 --> 00:19:17.581
Hurry up and get over here!

00:19:17.614 --> 00:19:18.516
- You're kidding.

00:19:18.550 --> 00:19:21.187
Why's he helping out
that scumbag?

00:19:21.221 --> 00:19:23.191
KENCHO: Akira!
What the hell?

00:19:23.225 --> 00:19:25.931
I thought you wanted nothing
to do with that jerk!

00:19:25.964 --> 00:19:27.968
- I don't, but...

00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:29.805
Standing by while
someone's about

00:19:29.838 --> 00:19:33.245
to get eaten alive by
zombies isn't something that's
on

00:19:33.278 --> 00:19:36.987
my bucket list!

00:19:37.020 --> 00:19:40.126
[both breathing heavily]

00:19:40.159 --> 00:19:41.562
Do it!

00:19:41.595 --> 00:19:43.498
[engine revving]

00:19:51.114 --> 00:19:54.353
[zombie groaning]

00:19:56.792 --> 00:19:57.861
[both gasping]

00:19:58.763 --> 00:20:00.266
[all chuckling]

00:20:00.299 --> 00:20:01.602
<i>MAN: We're
counting on you!</i>

00:20:01.636 --> 00:20:02.637
<i>AKIRA: Right!</i>

00:20:06.011 --> 00:20:07.246
Ready?

00:20:07.815 --> 00:20:08.984
Let's go!

00:20:09.017 --> 00:20:10.352
[KOSUGI gasps]
Let's go?

00:20:10.385 --> 00:20:12.290
Hold on, we're not gonna jump
from here, are we?

00:20:12.323 --> 00:20:15.830
- One, two, three!

00:20:23.746 --> 00:20:26.118
[both screaming]

00:20:26.151 --> 00:20:29.390
[zombies roaring]

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:34.835
- [whimpering]
- [gasping]

00:20:34.868 --> 00:20:36.806
KENCHO: Akira!

00:20:36.840 --> 00:20:38.877
[cackling]

00:20:38.910 --> 00:20:40.112
Amazing!

00:20:40.145 --> 00:20:41.883
MAN: Good job out there, newbie.

00:20:41.916 --> 00:20:43.318
MAN 2: That was incredible!

00:20:43.352 --> 00:20:44.588
MAN 3: Oh, thank you!
- [laughing]

00:20:44.622 --> 00:20:45.857
Well, I only pulled
it off thanks

00:20:45.891 --> 00:20:48.295
to your help.
KENCHO: Ah, don't be so modest.

00:20:48.329 --> 00:20:50.767
AKIRA: Oh, Shizuka!

00:20:50.801 --> 00:20:53.272
That was close,
but we pulled through all right!

00:20:53.305 --> 00:20:55.310
- Good grief.

00:20:55.343 --> 00:20:56.912
It's just like you...

00:20:57.981 --> 00:21:00.419
To always do something crazy.

00:21:00.452 --> 00:21:01.622
- It was nothin'.

00:21:01.655 --> 00:21:03.358
- Uh, that wasn't a compliment.

00:21:03.392 --> 00:21:04.929
- Huh?
- Oh.

00:21:04.962 --> 00:21:07.200
[both laughing]

00:21:07.233 --> 00:21:09.237
[KOSUGI laughing]

00:21:09.270 --> 00:21:12.578
As expected from
a loyal subordinate of mine!

00:21:12.611 --> 00:21:14.781
He was a fine example,
wasn't he?

00:21:14.815 --> 00:21:17.386
You should all take after Tendo
and from now on be--

00:21:17.419 --> 00:21:19.357
MAN: Yeah, sorry, Kosugi.
- Huh?

00:21:19.391 --> 00:21:21.194
- But I'm done workin'
for you,

00:21:21.227 --> 00:21:22.363
so consider this my resignation.

00:21:22.396 --> 00:21:23.599
- KOSUGI: What?

00:21:23.633 --> 00:21:25.168
- You made us do all
the hard work

00:21:25.202 --> 00:21:26.972
while you sit around
and do nothing!

00:21:27.006 --> 00:21:28.777
- You're terrible.
- And, uh,

00:21:28.810 --> 00:21:31.281
that newbie was a better leader
than you have ever been.

00:21:31.315 --> 00:21:32.617
[KOSUGI stammering]

00:21:32.651 --> 00:21:35.155
- Yeah, I think it's safe
to say we've more

00:21:35.189 --> 00:21:36.793
than paid our dues by now.

00:21:36.826 --> 00:21:39.364
- It's about time we pack up
and get a move on.

00:21:39.397 --> 00:21:40.733
- Thanks for everything, though!

00:21:40.767 --> 00:21:42.705
MAN: We're the ones who brought
this stuff in,

00:21:42.738 --> 00:21:44.307
so we're gonna haul it out.
- Wait, wait!

00:21:44.340 --> 00:21:45.811
MAN: I wanna go somewhere warm.
- Don't go!

00:21:45.844 --> 00:21:47.715
KOSUGI: You guys, wait!

00:21:47.748 --> 00:21:49.284
- Let's go.

00:21:49.317 --> 00:21:50.186
KOSUGI: I treated you all well,
didn't I?

00:21:50.219 --> 00:21:52.290
Wait, don't go!

00:21:52.323 --> 00:21:54.260
- [snickers]
- KOSUGI: Wait!

00:21:54.294 --> 00:21:57.601
Don't leave me here!

00:21:57.634 --> 00:21:59.805
[crying]

00:21:59.838 --> 00:22:02.009
[engines revving]

00:22:07.922 --> 00:22:09.457
SHIZUKA: Seriously?

00:22:09.490 --> 00:22:11.963
You really don't remember any
of it?

00:22:11.996 --> 00:22:14.000
- I kinda blacked out.

00:22:14.033 --> 00:22:16.438
Around Chief Kosugi,
I lost myself, you know?

00:22:16.472 --> 00:22:17.608
Like I wasn't there.

00:22:17.641 --> 00:22:19.512
[groans]

00:22:19.545 --> 00:22:22.518
That said,
manual labor really sucks.

00:22:22.551 --> 00:22:24.589
Maybe I'm not cut out for it.

00:22:24.622 --> 00:22:26.391
Nah, it's starting
to really feel like--

00:22:26.425 --> 00:22:29.063
like I'll never find
the right job.

00:22:29.097 --> 00:22:30.199
- So what?

00:22:30.232 --> 00:22:31.635
It's not like there's any rush

00:22:31.669 --> 00:22:34.474
to get a job right now.
- Huh?

00:22:34.508 --> 00:22:36.879
- Influencers,
esports athletes,

00:22:36.912 --> 00:22:38.950
drone pilots...

00:22:38.983 --> 00:22:41.455
Cool new jobs are created all
of the time,

00:22:41.488 --> 00:22:44.661
ones we couldn't imagine
100 years ago.

00:22:44.695 --> 00:22:46.331
SHIZUKA: We don't know
what tomorrow will bring

00:22:46.364 --> 00:22:47.466
in this world,

00:22:47.499 --> 00:22:49.738
or what kind of jobs there
will be.

00:22:49.772 --> 00:22:51.407
It's anyone's
guess, really.

00:22:52.443 --> 00:22:54.915
So do whatever you wanna do now.

00:22:54.948 --> 00:22:58.823
Just make sure you enjoy it
and savor every second of it.

00:22:58.857 --> 00:23:00.660
Eventually, one day,

00:23:00.693 --> 00:23:03.833
one of those things may become
a job that only you can do.

00:23:03.867 --> 00:23:05.335
- [grunts]

00:23:05.369 --> 00:23:07.774
<i>[Shiyui's
"Happiness of the Dead"]</i>

00:23:08.576 --> 00:23:09.845
<i>AKIRA: You're right!</i>

00:24:04.487 --> 00:24:06.825
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

